The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Ropar, Jan. 19 (PTI): An army man has been arrested for allegedly plotting to rob a bank.          
	Police said they had received information yesterday that Balvir Singh had stolen a colleagues rifle and ammunition. The police raided Singhs house and recovered the rifle. Singh was posted with 16 Sikh Regiment at Naushera in Jammu and Kashmir.                  
	 Jammu (PTI): Villagers on Monday killed a python and saved a three-year-old girl from its clutches on the outskirts of Jammu, police said. The 12-foot-long python had attacked Jano who was playing in the compound of her house. The python also tried to constrict her uncle when he tried to save her. Neighbours rushed to the place on hearing the commotion and killed the snake.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): About 50 domestic and international flights got delayed on Monday because of heavy fog at Indira Gandhi International airport. Fifteen flights were cancelled and 23 diverted. Runway visibility had dropped to 800 metres at 10pm on Sunday, and conditions deteriorated on Monday.                   
	 Raipur (PTI): Eleven inmates of a juvenile home in Raipur escaped on Monday while playing near the compound. Police have re-arrested one of them some 20km from the city and a search is on to nab the rest.                  
	Mumbai (PTI): Shah Rukh Khan is paying for the treatment of two orphans injured in a grenade attack in Srinagar. They are undergoing treatment at the Nanavati hospital in Mumbai. The actor, who had donated Rs 50 lakh to the childrens ward of the hospital, has visited the two children at the hospital.                  
	 Kochi (PTI): CPM leader and former Citu all-India president E. Balanandan died at a private hospital here on Monday. He was 84 and is survived by his wife, son and three daughters. Balanandan, a former Rajya Sabha member, was suffering from cancer.                                                                                                                           
